#: app/templates/partner/api_docs.html:344
msgid ""
"The umbrella for one reader-facing voting experience: headline title, how it"
" anchors to your site (<code>article_url</code> and/or "
"<code>external_id</code>), partner environment (test/live), one "
"embed/consensus URLs, and the combined participation underneath it. Creating"
" a discussion via API establishes this container first."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/partner/api_docs.html:348
msgid ""
"Individual prompts inside that umbrella — each collects its own agree / "
"disagree / unsure counts. Populate them during creation with "
"<code>seed_statements</code> or an <code>excerpt</code> that fuels AI seeds;"
" add/edit them afterward in the portal; optionally allow anonymous readers "
"to propose more when embed submissions are toggled on for that discussion."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/partner/api_docs.html:357
msgid ""
"The usual pattern is “one discussion per published URL,” but that is a "
"choice, not a requirement. You can create discussions for article pages, "
"attach a CMS id without a public article, or mix both so reporting stays "
"consistent across your stack."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/partner/api_docs.html:358
msgid ""
"Regardless of identifiers, remember the split: lookup/create returns "
"<code>discussion_id</code>; statements are modeled separately and surfaced "
"through the embed, portal statement tools, and snapshot payloads."
msgstr ""

