msgstr "Sigue los pasos a continuación para lanzar en tu sitio."

#: app/templates/partner/portal/getting_started.html:15
msgid "How this works — in plain terms"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/partner/portal/getting_started.html:16
msgid ""
"Society Speaks is a moderated voting box you place on pages you choose. You "
"decide the headline question and the opening statements readers see first; "
"we host the box, collect votes, and give you clear results — similar in "
"spirit to a structured poll, not an open comment thread."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/partner/portal/getting_started.html:18
msgid "Quick vocabulary"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/partner/portal/getting_started.html:20
msgid ""
"<strong>Discussion</strong> — one voting topic tied to a single embed: the "
"headline title, how it connects to your site, and one shared tally for that "
"topic."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/partner/portal/getting_started.html:21
msgid ""
"<strong>Statements</strong> — the individual lines readers rate with agree /"
" disagree / unsure inside that discussion; expect several per topic, not "
"just one."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/partner/portal/getting_started.html:25
msgid ""
"Tell us each website address where the voting box may appear — we prove you "
"control it with a one-line DNS step (similar to verifying email)."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/partner/portal/getting_started.html:26
msgid ""
"You create each “discussion” yourself (in the portal or via your tech team’s"
" automation): a title, a link to an article <em>and/or</em> your own stable "
"CMS id, plus either statements your editors draft or a short excerpt so we "
"can suggest balanced <strong>statements</strong> for that discussion. We do "
"not crawl your site or invent topics for you."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/partner/portal/getting_started.html:27
msgid ""
"You paste a small embed snippet on the page. Readers vote without leaving "
"your site; optional notifications can update your systems automatically."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/partner/portal/getting_started.html:29
msgid ""
"Not technical? Share this page with engineering and keep the DNS emails "
"handy — they only need to do the domain step once per hostname."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/partner/portal/getting_started.html:34
msgid ""
"Admin preview mode (read-only) — this is the partner guided setup "
"experience."
msgstr ""
"Modo de vista previa para administradores (solo lectura) — esta es la "
"experiencia de configuración guiada para socios."

#: app/templates/partner/portal/getting_started.html:50
msgid "Important setup note"
msgstr "Nota importante de configuración"

#: app/templates/partner/portal/getting_started.html:51
msgid ""
"Anything that creates or changes discussions must run from <strong>your "
"servers</strong>, not from a browser — that keeps your secret keys safe. "
"Free “read” checks can still be tried from ordinary web tools."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/partner/portal/getting_started.html:52
msgid ""
"Technical detail: <code>POST/PATCH /api/partner/...</code> rejects browser-"
"origin requests."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/partner/portal/getting_started.html:57
msgid ""
"<strong>Newsroom workflow:</strong> use <code>external_id</code> for CMS "
"mapping, webhook callbacks for downstream sync, and team roles in the portal"
" for controlled access."
msgstr ""
"<strong>Flujo de sala de prensa:</strong> usa <code>external_id</code> para "
"mapeo de CMS, devoluciones de llamada de webhooks para sincronización "
"descendente, y roles de equipo en el portal para acceso controlado."

#: app/templates/partner/portal/getting_started.html:60
msgid ""
